{"id": "EUVD-2025-32879", "enisaUuid": "f4745b4d-70bb-36d7-85ef-e5dbc477a01d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ngenetlink: fix genl_bind() invoking bind() after -EPERM\n\nPer family bind/unbind callbacks were introduced to allow families\nto track multicast group consumer presence, e.g. to start or stop\nproducing events depending on listeners.\n\nHowever, in genl_bind() the bind() callback was invoked even if\ncapability checks failed and ret was set to -EPERM. This means that\ncallbacks could run on behalf of unauthorized callers while the\nsyscall still returned failure to user space.\n\nFix this by only invoking bind() after \"if (ret) break;\" check\ni.e. after permission checks have succeeded.", "datePublished": "2025-10-01T09:30:25", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-11T18:30:35", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-39926", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1dbfb0363224f6da56f6655d596dc5097308d6f5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8858c1e9405906c09589d7c336f04058ea198207", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/98c9d884047a3051c203708914a874dece3cbe54"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-39926", "GHSA-f9wm-ppg2-pc92"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0f7335ce-8e77-32f5-aa28-c07f6420f73e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.48"}, {"id": "2627b61d-e1d9-3bbc-b3ab-fba23e956e89", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "3f564b8e-51c6-3f90-8856-0458c3a71e2b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.8"}, {"id": "95bbe87d-8295-387c-b23b-2e44734a1e65", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "9f25da39-69fe-3449-ab03-f5423ad70d59", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3de21a8990d3c2cc507e9cc4ed00f36358d5b93e <8858c1e9405906c09589d7c336f04058ea198207"}, {"id": "cec7aa2a-9222-342e-888f-63e0d970363c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.9"}, {"id": "cedb716f-699a-3f70-bdbb-5b95a93fea2c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3de21a8990d3c2cc507e9cc4ed00f36358d5b93e <98c9d884047a3051c203708914a874dece3cbe54"}, {"id": "e3524d06-3c9e-346d-be4b-f2d6bfa52a70", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3de21a8990d3c2cc507e9cc4ed00f36358d5b93e <1dbfb0363224f6da56f6655d596dc5097308d6f5"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "59fc2e81-6e46-3a10-ad39-d183c2441774", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}